==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosher
<hw>Cosh"er</hw> <pr>(k?sh"?r)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Ir.
<ets>cosair</ets> a feast, a banquet? or cf. F. <ets>coucher</ets> to
lie. Cf. <er>Couch</er>, <er>Coshering</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Old Law)</fld> <def>To levy certain exactions or tribute upon; to
lodge and eat at the expense of. See <er>Coshering</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To treat with hospitality; to pet.</def>
<mark>[Ireland]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cosherer</ent>⟦br⟧
